						<h3 class='content_title'>Hollywood Data Explorer</h3>

						<div class='content_body'>
						
							<div class='col1'>

								<a href="http://indexity.net/vis/hw"><img src='/assets/data_explorer.png'></a>


							</div>
							<div class="col2">

										<p>An entry into the <a href='http://www.informationisbeautifulawards.com/2012/03/hall-of-fame-hollywood-challenge-winners/'>Information is Beautiful Hollywood Challenge</a>.
											
											This highly interactive web application is designed to explore some of the metrics coming out of Hollywood. The tool covers over 500 films from the past 5 years.
												</p>	
												
												<p>
													The data explorer specifically takes a neutral stance, and allows the users to draw their own conclusions.  There are literally thousands of possible combinations.
													
												</p>	
											
										
										<p>	Build with lots of <a href='http://d3js.org'>d3</a> and jQuery.  Placed 2nd place in the interactive category.
											
											</p>
